,Recommended,285330,33188004,Posted: 3 July,all,Lycangel,"Ok so I've heard a lot of people are having trouble starting it up! Here's what you can do.open the Control Panel (you can do it by using WinKey+X key combination) go to Programs > Programs and Features, click the Turn Windows features on or off link, find the Legacy components on the list, enable DirectPlay and click OK to install it.After you have done that, go to your Rollercoaster Tycoon file, should be in something like this....D:\Program Files (x86)\Steam\steamapps\common\Rollercoaster Tycoon 2Mines in the D: drive normally its in C: though. Find the .exe and right click it and go to ""Troubleshoot compatability"" use whatever setting it comes up with. That SHOULD fix it! Hopefully this helps folks because this really is a fun little game to play."
