,Recommended,285330,21825747,"Posted: 13 March, 2016",all,DarK_St3alth,"Rank:8/10Recommendation(s):Don’t expect to play a classic on new systems.Major Theme:Old school means it doesn’t need any schooling.Bought at Price:$5.99 (Steam Sale)I might be one of the select few to have actually played this game with real CDs (yes CDs… Not DVDs). Rollercoaster Tycoon 1 and 2 were my go to games before I joined Steam.Maybe it’s the simplicity of the title, or the enjoyment of charging people to go to the bathroom. Whatever the case might be, if you have an older system you are likely to enjoy this title.If you happened to give into Microsoft marketing and upgraded to 8/8.1/10, you should seek OpenRCT2 in addition. RC2 is a game built in assembly (really, just look at the system requirements) it will almost be required for you to use OpenRCT2 to play this title.The game plays out of the box on Windows 7, but beware that it uses a lower color depth, and alt+tab users should not be alarmed by the change in color modes.Resolutions are also minimally supported, the max usable for 16:9 users being 720. Obviously, you aren’t playing this game for the “leading” graphics.All the other later games in the series personally don’t seem to add anything meaningful, so I’d advise you to just grab RC2 and leave it at that."
