,Recommended,285330,13170881,"Posted: 30 November, 2014",all,Frogs are People Too,"PROS:-It's Rollercoaster Tycoon-It's pretty much the same as the first game except with more stuff, meaning they didn't ruin everything. The ATM and boatload of scenery is especially a nice touch-I've read it's considered the ""best"" Rollercoaster Tycoon, meaning there's likely a healthy supply of fanmade content for the gameCONS:-20 second long crowd noise loop still irritating as hell. ""ROLLER COASTER"" ""BUT WHYYYYY"" ""EHAHAHAHAHA. BWAAAHH. OOOHOOOOHOOOHOOO."" It was cute for nostalgic reasons for about 2 minutes before I wished they made a longer, more varied sound for crowded areas-It's pretty much the same as the first game except with more stuff, meaning they didn't seem to add that much-The scenarios suck my toes. Almost all of the ones I've tried so far make you wonder if they even put any thought into making them. Half the time the existing rides don't even have names. The scenery looks good (or, at least, it probably did back in the day, so I'm trying to judge it on that) but most of the time it just gets in the way. Sometimes guests get lost on thepre-existing paths. You rarely allowed to charge per ride so you're stuck entirely relying on vendors and admission fees. Give me Forest Frontiers or Dynamite Dunes over Alcatraz and Rio anyday-Maybe I haven't figured it out yet but it seems like there's no way to access the Steam community inside the game, which makes playing while you're chatting with someone a pain in the neck.Overall, despite my criticisms, it's cheap and fun and it's in no way worse than the original (aside from the scenarios). If you're asking yourself if you want to pick it up, you probably do."
