,Recommended,285330,17521177,"Posted: 13 August, 2015",all,NPersival,"Ooooh boy, the memories! Just hearing that music gave me chills down my back and draw a smile upon my face as if I were a 10 years old version of me playing it for the first time again.- For those who played any RCT before:So... RCT2, what´s to say about it? In a nutshell it´s basically RCT1 with more attractions, bigger parks, some minor tweaks here and there and more customization for you to play around like choosing the music for the rides.- For those who never played any RCT before:This is a game so simple that is perfect, yes it´s a 2D with ISO camera game but don´t let that get in your way of playing this as that same two things are the ones that will let you play this game in ANY computer from a pentium 4 to an i7 beast. If you like the tycoon genre or simulation games this is just for you as it puts you in the shoes of the one in charge of making and managing a theme park, you will find yourself placing your first ride and choosing the location, price, colour, music, decoration and the themes for it, then you place an information kiosk or a souvenir stall and you find that it lets you even choose the colour of the umbrella or t-shirt you are selling, once you are done with that you realize that you need a handyman and a mechanic to keep the park up and running so you open the staff window just to see that you can choose the staff colour and uniform! (in the case of the entertainer). What is my point with all this? To let you know that you shouldn´t turn this game down for the fact that is a 2D old game, HECK NO! This game enables you to make any park you want, your imagination is the limit!To sum up, this game is easily my favourite of all time, it´s incredible that being that old it still holds up agains time and keeps making me spend hours and hours on it like the first time I played it. This is for those who knows that a good game is based on good game mechanics instead of pretty graphics (so I wouldn´t recommend a 12 years old buying it as the first thing he is gonna say it´s ""this game is awful, look at those graphics!""), so if you played RCT1 and you liked it BUY THIS, if you like drowning the people who hate your park BUY IT (yes, you can do that), if you like making crazy roller coasters that crashes into a mountain BUY IT (you can also do that), if you don´t mind the 2D graphics and ISO camera BUY IT, this game is a no brainer and you will spend tons of hours on it without even realizing it, trust me.10/10"
