,Recommended,285330,11443777,"Posted: 27 July, 2014",all,SubrosianChainsawMassacre_|BC|,"I had this game on CD-rom when I was a kid, and it still works on my old computer, but now that it's on steam, I can play it much easier and have just as much fun as I did when I was younger.The point of the game is to create amusment parks and build rides to complete a specific goal, if you don't your park gets shut down. It's not something you think would be fun to play, but it is. You get to completely customize how your rides are built, you decide where people can walk, whether your guests live or drown in the nearest pool of water, you can even create a park designed to make your guests suffer an untimely demise. All that with the ability to create your own parks with their own objectives, there's plenty to keep you entertained.The game isn't perfect though, removing unneeded footpaths can be slightly annoying due to the isometric camera angle and somewhat picky programming, but it's nothing that makes the game even slightly less fun.If you haven't experienced this game yet, pick it up, you'll surely enjoy yourself. After all, what other game lets you build your own six flags parks, or build parks on volcanoes or prison islands?"
