,Recommended,285330,16232268,"Posted: 6 June, 2015",all,Crabs,"This is the quintessential time consumer simulation game. I'd say it plays just as well as I remember, but I've been playing it every since the day the first game was released. It takes everything the first game had, polishes every aspect of it, and throws a ton of new content in that never gets old. The unique visual style has barely aged a day, and the music will burrow its way right back into your brain. And that's just the base game.Possibly the best reason for buying this game digitally was the advent of OpenRCT2, a massive project that overhauls the game from the ground up, reworking it from assembly code to an increasingly easy to modify open-source software. It's created a limitless world for game modifications, from new maps and scenarios, new scenery, new ride and vehicle types, and tons of UI and technical improvements. There are even lovingly recreated versions of the scenarios from the first game - essentially giving you 1 and 2 for the price of just this game. Most importantly. the game can now run at 60 FPS at a 4k resolution; even 1080 was impossible for the base game, making playing on any setup incredibly simple. It even removes all compatibility issues with newer operation systems.RollerCoaster Tycoon 2 is a game that can only stand to get better and better with age."
