,Recommended,285330,25511367,"Posted: 15 September, 2016",all,Selah,"An amazing game for anyone interested in business sims, building sims, or just messing around in a theme park environment. The entire game is a blast, but some of my favorite game elements are: 1) designing awesome rollercoasters and other rides like go karts and water rides; 2) getting feedback from visitors and being able to use it to improve your park, 3) the general chatter and noise the people make is endearing, and 4) watching someone exit a ride that they love, and jumping in the air in excitement.I don't have a problem with (well done) games where you are basically just shifting around resources and reviewing spreadsheets, but this goes beyond that type of game, with a great balance between building, financial matters, employee guidance, visitor interactivity, and other matters.There's no major flaws IMO, but certain things might not be everyone's cup of tea. First, it can be a slow and leisurely game to play; Second, while it doesn't require a ton of micromanagement, nonetheless if you aren't willing to do at least *some* in-depth stuff (esp. with your workers) your park can become a mess; Third, the graphics and art are not bright and shiny and cartoonish in the way that a lot of business sims are (though for someone like me, this is a positive rather than a negative); Fourth, it's not in 3d, but like a 2.5d where you can look at things from 4 perspectives, and this can make seeing certain things difficult at times.Anyway, to sum up... if you are at all interested in this genre or theme, it'll almost certainly be worth it to get this. Go!"
