,Recommended,285330,31670880,Posted: 10 May,all,Vortiene,"tl;dr: get the OpenRCT2 mod.Do yourself a favor, forget about more recent theme park simulators, forget about sequels to this game that tried to take it into 3D, this one is the definitive theme park simulator. There's a point at which something becomes so perfected that there's no reason to try to make a better version of it. It rarely happens in games, but RCT2, particularly with the OpenRCT2 mod, becomes the perfect theme park simulator game. After the mod, you have 1080p, 60fps, steam integration. Less crashes than the vanilla game. Autosaving. Quality-of-life fixes. Seriously, just check it out:https://github.com/OpenRCT2/OpenRCT2/wiki/Changes-to-original-gameThe visuals are timeless, look great, and are actually more straighforward to play with on a isometric grid rather than in complete 3 dimensions, especially when designing paths and tracks. Now count in the countless mods for the game, new rides, endless scenarios, porting of RCT1 scenarios, and the ridiculous amount of hours you can spend finishing even just the vanilla game scenarios, you've got a game for the ages.Sometimes I hear the question: ""If you were put in jail for 3 years and had no internet but could choose 1 game to play, what would it be?"" This game. The amount of content and time you can put into it is higher than almost any other offline game. What's more, with very simple mods you can also join other players in online play.As I said, this game has reached perfection due to the community around it. You don't need another theme park simulator. This one is all you will ever need, due to it's incredible depth of features and the enthusiastic open-source community behind it."
