,Recommended,285330,30182625,Posted: 25 February,all,Ｈｅｎｋｅ３７,"Wow. This is the worst game release on steam I've ever seen. It crashes instantly when I try and launch it and the original installer is even included. What were they thinking?No, throw away the provided executable and use OpenRCT2 instead. That works flawlessly.Yet, at the same time, this is an excellent game. This is really nothing more than version 2.0 of the original Roller Coaster Tycoon. Same great game, but with some new features. This game could just as easily have been an expansion pack.Building attractions is always fun and there are plenty of scenarios to try. But it does kinda samey rather quickly. Seen one scenario, seen them all. Built one roller coaster, built them all. It is unquestionably still fun, but it gets repetitive rather quickly. This is a game you can fire up for a few hours when you are bored and need a little hobby project to work on for a while.One thing I noticed with the scenarios compared to the original is the overuse of decorative objects. You can easily get several thousand bucks just from removing the unmanageble messes that the scenarios come with. The issue isn't just the overuse, it's the type of unmanageable structures built for you. It is pretty much always hollow shells that are a pain to work with. Trying to edit them or put tracks/roads into them is an exercise in futility. They are built to look nice, not to be worked with.One thing I noticed is that it rarely matters what you build. Just build one of everything and guests will be happy. Maybe it gets more challenging with harder scenarios, but I doubt it. Ultimately the guests are very simple state machines that don't care about your attractions beyond the three key statistics for each one. It works, but it doesn't give a lot of depth.But overall? This is a great game. It's easy to forget the systems it runs on and just have fun working on a little pet project for a few hours."
